Package au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.collections.tables

Interface Table

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.DataContainer, fr.ens.biologie.generic.SaveableAsText, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Showable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sizeable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BooleanTable, ByteTable, CharTable, DoubleTable, FloatTable, IntTable, LongTable, ObjectTable, ShortTable, StringTable, TableAdapter
    public interface Table
extends fr.ens.biologie.generic.DataContainer, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sizeable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Showable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.SaveableAsText

    An interface for multidimensional access to data. Basically there are three ways to access the data

    1. by multidimensional integer indexes (eg (i1,i2,i3);
    2. by flat index, i.e. a single index k computed as k = f(i1,i2,i3 ,n1,n2,n3) where ni's are the sizes of each dimension and f is a clever function doing the computation for you;
    3. by multidimensional non-integer indexes (this is optional and decided at construction time).
    Author:
    J. Gignoux - 15 f√©vr. 2017
